text: Staveley-in-Cartmel is a village and civil parish in South Lakeland, Cumbria, England. In 2001 there were 428 people living in Staveley-in-Cartmel. It has 22 listed buildings. It has a church called St Mary. == References == Category:Villages in Cumbria Category:Civil parishes in Cumbria
title: Staveley-in-Cartmel
